\cos^2(z)+\sin^2(z)=(\cos(z)+i\sin(z))(\cos(z)-i\sin(z))=e^{iz}e^{-iz}=1
 \sin z = \sin(x+iy)=\sin(x)\cos(iy)+\sin(iy)\cos(x),\quad i=\sqrt{-1}. 
 \implies \sin z = \sin(x) \cosh(y)+i\sinh(y)\cos(x). 
